{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is now integrated with the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-navigation"},{"type":"text","text":" library,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which brings powerful navigation and observation tools to UIKit. You can model your domains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as concisely as possible, just as you would in SwiftUI, but then implement your view in UIKit"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without losing any power.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The simplest tool to use is ","type":"text"},{"code":"observe","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which allows you to minimally observe changes to state in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"your feature and update the UI. Typically the best place to do this is in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"viewDidLoad"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let store: StoreOf<Feature>","","func viewDidLoad() {","  super.viewDidLoad()","","  \/\/ ...","","  observe { [weak self] in","    countLabel.text = \"Count: \\(store.count)\"","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Only the state accessed in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observe"},{"type":"text","text":" trailing closure will be observed. If any other state"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes, the closure will not be invoked and no extra work will be performed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The library also provides powerful navigation tools for UIKit. For example, suppose you have a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"feature that can present a child feature (see the docs on ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitle":"tree-based navigation","isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TreeBasedNavigation","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"tree-based","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"navigation"}]},{"text":" for more information on these tools):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer ","struct Feature {","  @ObservableState","  struct State {","    @Presents var child: ChildFeature.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then you can present a view controller when the child state flips to a non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value by using the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"present(item:)"},{"type":"text","text":" API that comes with the library:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@UIBindable var store: StoreOf<Feature>","","func viewDidLoad() {","  super.viewDidLoad()","","  present(item: $store.scope(state: \\.child, action: \\.child)) { store in","    ChildViewController(store: store)","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Further, if your feature has a stack of features that can be presented, then you can model your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"domain like so (see the docs on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackBasedNavigation","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"stack-based","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"stack-based"}],"type":"reference"},{"text":" for more information","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on these tools):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@Reducer","struct AppFeature {","  struct State {","    var path = StackState<Path.State>()","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  @Reducer","  enum Path {","    case addItem(AddFeature)","    case detailItem(DetailFeature)","    case editItem(EditFeature)","  }","","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And for the view you can subclass ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStackController"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to drive navigation from the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stack state:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["class AppController: NavigationStackController {","  private var store: StoreOf<AppFeature>!","","  convenience init(store: StoreOf<AppFeature>) {","    @UIBindable var store = store","","    self.init(path: $store.scope(state: \\.path, action: \\.path)) {","      RootViewController(store: store)","    } destination: { store in ","      switch store.case {","      case .addItem(let store):","        AddViewController(store: store)","      case .detailItem(let store):","        DetailViewController(store: store)","      case .editItem(let store):","        EditViewController(store: store)","      }","    }","","    self.store = store","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.13","role":"article"},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/document